13/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey is firmly resolved to combat human trafficking and has adopted relevant regulations on the issue in addition to approving all related international agreements, said Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul in an official letter published Tuesday (12 August). 
Turkey ratified the UN Convention Against Transnational Organised Crime and additional protocols on 18 March. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 12/08/03)
